Defendant Christopher A Melk in court with attorney Valeria Lenise Taylor.  Christopher Allen Liegel appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. Parties are prepared to proceed. Packet of photos submitted by attorney Taylor received and filed. Statements made as to sentencing. Additional statements made by Charles M. 

As to COUNT 1 as AMENDED-
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction with release for work and school if enrolled in educational program; credit for 1 day time served.

If revoked, court costs, fees and surcharges be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b).

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 2 YEARS with the following conditions:

1) Court ordered 30 days of condition time in the House of Correction imposed and stayed to be used at the discretion of the agent;
2) Maintain full time employment, or be enrolled in full time educational program, or maintain part time employment and part time educational program;
3) No unsupervised contact with children under the age of 16 years;
4) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
5) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge; 
6) Court set restitution at ZERO;
7) Cooperate with all rules as set forth by probation agent;
8) Court finds no additional programming is necessary other that the programs that the defendant is currently participating in. Any additional programming to be at the discretion of the agent;
9) No contact with the victim or the victim's mother;

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession; Voting 

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
